- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category, as the paper proposes a new approach to quantify and compare graph evolutions. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) could be another possible category, as the paper deals with the dynamics of complex systems (i.e., networks). 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category, as the paper introduces a new measure (centrality distance) to compare graphs. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible category, as the paper deals with the evolution of networks over time.
